{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:31:48.309980+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"apply_migrations.sh applies files in wrong order on filesystems with case-folding\",\"body\":\"---\\n\\nUpdate: I tried to narrow this down with a fresh local reset, but I\\nmay still be missing something environment-specific:\\n\\n  $ rm -rf .pgdata\\n  $ docker compose up -d\\n  $ ./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\\n  Applying migrations/003_add_session_index.sql\\n  ...\\n  ERROR:  relation \\u0026#34;sessions\\u0026#34; does not exist\\n\\nI saw this twice on my workstation (macOS 14.5, zsh 5.9, APFS,\\nLANG=en_US.UTF-8), but I haven\\u0026#39;t yet reproduced it inside a clean\\ncontainer shell or captured the raw `echo migrations/*.sql` expansion.\\nGiven how core migration ordering is to onboarding, I\\u0026#39;d suggest this\\ngets the `bug` and `priority/high` labels if a maintainer can confirm.\\nHappy to write the sorted-loop patch if that would help.\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:33Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:36Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMzozM1rPAAAAAQwoXWA=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMzozM1rPAAAAAQwoXWA=\"}}", "id": "lc_b544008c-cb53-45ab-bc6f-4ea163d22220"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "f8cc6cba-2a92-4414-99d3-08991bec872e", "tool_call_id": "call_9d39e759349942228be58e0e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
